    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Problem description.</h3>\n<p>\u00a0There is a village in which lives a number of tribes. Different Kind of tribe is represented by a different color and same kind of tribe is represented by same color .  But there is a problem that no two tribes of same color can live adjacent to each other and they get destroyed immediately,\nand new tribes joins to form a straight line.In one operation all such adjacent tribes gets destroyed simultaneously. Again the procedure continues until there is no such tribes to be destroyed and peace is restored in the village.\nGiven that all the tribes of the villages fall in a straight line you have to count how many such operations will it take for the village to be in peace once again.\n</p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>the first line of the input contains a single integer t denoting the number of test cases.\nFirst line of each test case contains a number denoting the size of the string of village .\nSecond line contains a single string containing lower case alphabets only denoting different color tribes.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Output a single integer for each test case denoting the number of operations it would take for the village to attain peace.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<p>Should contain all the constraints on the input data that you may have. Format it like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>100000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>L</b> \u2264 <b>1000</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n6\naabaa\n5\nabban\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n1\n2\n\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n",
